Wararayuq (Quechua warara horn, -yuq a suffix to indicate ownership, "the one with a horn", Hispanicized spelling Huararayoc) is a  mountain in the Paryaqaqa mountain range in the Andes of Peru. It is located in the Lima Region, Huarochir√≠ Province, Quinti District. Wararayuq lies northwest of Qullqi P'ukru.
